ğŸ§ª Hands-on Project: â€œSend Email on S3 File Uploadâ€
This is your project listed earlier.
Below is the exact step-by-step explanation and why each step is needed.

ğŸ”¥ Step 1 â€” Create SNS Topic
Go to:
SNS â†’ Topics â†’ Create Topic

Choose:


Type: Standard


Name: s3-file-upload-topic


This topic is the broadcast channel where S3 will publish events.

ğŸ”¥ Step 2 â€” Add Email Subscription
Go to:
SNS â†’ Topic â†’ Subscriptions â†’ Create Subscription



Protocol: Email


Endpoint: your-email@example.com


AWS sends a verification email â†’ click â€œConfirm subscriptionâ€.
Now SNS knows your email is a valid receiver.

ğŸ”¥ Step 3 â€” Configure S3 Event Notification
Go to:
S3 â†’ Bucket â†’ Properties â†’ Event notifications â†’ Create event

Event details:


Event: PUT (upload)


Prefix: optionally "uploads/"


Destination: SNS topic


Select: s3-file-upload-topic


Now the chain looks like:
S3 upload â†’ SNS topic â†’ sends email


